instance virtual_to_physical_interaction : DTDFVocab:VirtualToPhysical [
    base:desc "Commands originate in the User Interface FE (Control Panel) and are sent to the Digital Twin Entity’s Controlling FE, which implements the ACC algorithm (lead‑vehicle detection and desired‑speed computation). The resulting desired speed, as well as remote‑management commands (ACC enable/disable, speed set‑point change, emergency‑brake) are transmitted over the same UDP‑over‑Wi‑Fi link to the Physical Twin Entity where the Actuation FE converts the desired speed into motor voltage commands and drives the steering servo. Vehicle feedback (actual speed, steering angle, object tracks) is sent back through the ROS 2 network to close the control loop."
]

instance twinning_time_scale : DTDFVocab:TimeScale [
    base:desc "The DTS requires a shared notion of time between the physical vehicle and the digital twin; clock synchronization must achieve 100 ms accuracy (standards for safety‑critical vehicular applications are stricter, but hardware limits this system to 100 ms). All services—Data Monitoring, Computation Offloading of the ACC algorithm, and Remote Management—depend on low end‑to‑end latency communication over Wi‑Fi/UDP, and on real‑time updates of vehicle state, object tracks and projected driving path to support ACC operation."
]

instance dt_constellation : DTDFVocab:Constellation [
