instance dt_hosting_deployment : DTDFVocab:Deployment [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin System is partitioned across heterogeneous hardware. The Physical Twin Entity (vehicle) hosts the Data Pre‑Processing FE and Actuation FE as ROS 2 packages on the on‑board compute node. The Digital Twin Entity (ACC, Visualization, Data Collection, Reporting) runs on external compute resources—implicitly cloud or edge servers—because the ACC workload is off‑loaded from the vehicle. Collected ego‑vehicle state and object tracks are stored in an external SQL database (Data Storage FE). Scalability is achieved by allocating the ACC service to better‑suited external resources, while the architecture does not detail specific deployment models or redundancy mechanisms."
