    base:desc "The digital twin system acknowledges safety‑critical requirements by referencing automotive standards. The case study (Document 2) notes that the ISO 23247 reference architecture does not natively address safety, and recommends promoting safety to a first‑class citizen by applying the functional‑safety standard ISO 26262. The ACC function implemented in the DTS follows the performance‑class I requirements of ISO 15622 (Document 5), employing the basic control strategy defined in sections 6.1‑6.2 for a 1/10‑scale vehicle. These references provide a basis for safety risk assessment, fail‑safe actuation and compliance with established automotive safety standards, although no specific cybersecurity protocols or access‑control mechanisms are described."
